{"id":1454,"date":"2023-02-07T10:30:48","date_gmt":"2023-02-07T10:30:48","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/?p=1454"},"modified":"2023-08-12T08:04:08","modified_gmt":"2023-08-12T08:04:08","slug":"uk-tuition-fees-and-living-costs-for-international-students","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/uk-tuition-fees-and-living-costs-for-international-students\/","title":{"rendered":"UK Tuition Fees and Living Costs for International Students"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The United Kingdom has always been one of the favorite destinations for international students. To make everything more clear for all the students who are planning to continue their studies in one of the most prominent countries in the world, we&#8217;ve written this post with all you should know about UK tuition fees and living costs for international students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In this guide:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University Tuition Charges in the UK<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Student Living Costs in the UK<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University Scholarships and Grants<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Most Affordable Universities in the United Kingdom<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Conclusion<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1565\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/panoramic-view-big-ben-london-sunset-uk-1.jpg\" alt=\"UK Tuition Fees\" width=\"1145\" height=\"479\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/panoramic-view-big-ben-london-sunset-uk-1.jpg 1145w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/panoramic-view-big-ben-london-sunset-uk-1-300x126.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/panoramic-view-big-ben-london-sunset-uk-1-1024x428.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/panoramic-view-big-ben-london-sunset-uk-1-768x321.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1145px) 100vw, 1145px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University Tuition Charges in the UK<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The United Kingdom like any other country in the world, has its own educational system and financial aspect of it. Up until now, you could be charged two types of tuition fees in the United Kingdom:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">the home status fee: in general, these are lower fees, paid by local students, Irish citizens, and students from the EU, EEA, and Switzerland,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">the international fee: higher fees, which are sometimes 2 or 3 times higher, paid by all the remaining non-EU\/EEA students from all over the world.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Following Brexit, things changed significantly. Here are the main factors you need to know if you&#8217;re from the EU\/EEA or Switzerland and plan to begin studying in the UK after 1 January 2022:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">If you arrive in the UK after 1 January 2022 and start your study program before 31 July 2022, you will still enjoy the &#8216;home fee status,&#8217; and you&#8217;ll have the option to apply for a student loan.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Arrive in the UK after 1 January 2022 and start your study program after 1 August 2022. You will NOT enjoy the &#8216;home fee status&#8217; anymore, you won&#8217;t have access to student loans, and you&#8217;ll need to pay the total tuition fees established by each university individually.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These changes do not apply to Irish citizens or students who have started their courses before implementing this new policy.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">UK Tuition Fees for Public Institutions<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">At public UK universities, tuition costs may vary a lot. The home fee usually ranges from 5,500 to 10,200 EUR per year. It depends on the university, the type of program, and the length of studies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The international fee usually adds another 3000 to 8000 EUR to the initial home fee. It might be 2 or 3 times higher than the home fee in some cases.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This is all about public universities available to domestic and international student, but what about the private ones?<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">UK Tuition Fees for Private Universities<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">While some study programs at private universities have tuition costs comparable to those at public institutions, it&#8217;s generally true that private higher education is more expensive. Additionally, these institutions often don&#8217;t differentiate between EU\/EEA and non-EU\/EEA citizens.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students can pay anywhere from 5000 to over 35,000 EUR per academic year. At both public and private universities, Business and Medical studies are the most expensive.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">if you want to know about <a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/top-10-cheapest-cities-for-living\/\">Top 10 Cheapest Cities for Living<\/a> read this article:<\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"15LJyiFIan\"><p><a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/top-10-cheapest-cities-for-living\/\">Top 10 Cheapest Cities for Living<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;Top 10 Cheapest Cities for Living&#8221; &#8212; Abroadin \" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/top-10-cheapest-cities-for-living\/embed\/#?secret=vOqvOWs3SJ#?secret=15LJyiFIan\" data-secret=\"15LJyiFIan\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Student Living Costs in the UK<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.mastersportal.com\/articles\/2906\/tuition-fees-and-living-costs-in-the-uk-in-2023.html#:~:text=Student%20living%20costs%20in%20the%20UK&amp;text=In%20popular%20cities%20like%20London,the%20pound%20sterling%20(GBP).\">Living as a student in the UK<\/a> isn&#8217;t exactly cheap, but how much you end up spending depends on where you are planning to live.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In big cities like London, monthly living costs can quickly jump over 1500 EUR (about 1360 GBP). In smaller cities, you can live with a budget of 700 to 1200 EUR (about 635 to 1040 GBP) per month.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The national currency here is the pound sterling (GBP). At the time of writing this article, 4.55 GBP equals around 5 EUR.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1568\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/backpacker-using-her-phone-hostel-varanasi-india-1.jpg\" alt=\"UK Tuition Fees\" width=\"1400\" height=\"935\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/backpacker-using-her-phone-hostel-varanasi-india-1.jpg 1400w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/backpacker-using-her-phone-hostel-varanasi-india-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/backpacker-using-her-phone-hostel-varanasi-india-1-1024x684.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/backpacker-using-her-phone-hostel-varanasi-india-1-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Student Accommodation Costs<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Many universities in the UK provide student residence halls. These living spaces offer great value for money and include the costs of utilities in the overall price. Student residence halls are most popular among first-year students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">After the first academic year, many future graduates choose to rent a private space, either alone or with other peers. This option is more expensive, but it offers a more accurate sense of what it is like to live in the real world:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">one-bedroom apartment outside the city center: 610 GBP per month<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">one-bedroom apartment in the city center: 740 GBP per month<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">three-bedroom apartment outside the city center: 975 GBP per month<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">three-bedroom apartment in the city center: 1255 GBP per month<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Monthly utilities will add another 90 to 160 GBP to your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.thecompleteuniversityguide.co.uk\/student-advice\/before-you-start\/how-much-does-uni-accommodation-cost#:~:text=The%20average%20cost%20for%20weekly,259%20for%20the%20private%20sector\">accommodation expenses<\/a>.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Food Costs in the UK<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students will spend between 150 and 250 GBP on food and groceries. If you eat out and order food often, this budget will go up quickly.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The following are some of the average prices for food products in the United Kingdom.<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">12 eggs: 1.95 GBP,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">1 liter of milk: 0.90 GBP,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">1 kg of apples: 1.80 GBP,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">One loaf of bread: 1 GBP,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">1 kg of bananas: 1.10 GBP,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">1 kg of local cheese: 5.60 GBP,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">One meal at affordable restaurants: 12 GBP.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Transportation Costs; UK Tuition Fees<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To commute daily, you can choose from various means of public transport; and most of them offer discounts to students or young people in general.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These discounts might vary from one area or city to another, but here are a few examples:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Bus: 1.50 to 2.50 GBP for a one-way ticket,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Subway: 30% discount for +18 years old students who buy the Oyster Student Card,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Train: 30% discount for full-time students who buy a Young Persons Card, which usually costs 30 GBP.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Extra Charges for Everyday Life in the UK<\/span><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">entertainment, like cinema, concerts, theatre: 50 to 100 GBP per month,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">student visa fee: 348 GBP, which is one-time fee,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">IHS (Immigration Health Surcharge), which gives you access to the UK&#8217;s National Health Service: 470 GBP per year.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1567\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/young-english-teacher-doing-her-class-online-1.jpg\" alt=\"UK Tuition Fees\" width=\"1126\" height=\"751\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/young-english-teacher-doing-her-class-online-1.jpg 1126w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/young-english-teacher-doing-her-class-online-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/young-english-teacher-doing-her-class-online-1-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/young-english-teacher-doing-her-class-online-1-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1126px) 100vw, 1126px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University Scholarships and Grants<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In the United Kingdom, international students can apply for numerous scholarships and other types of financial support.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">To be successful, you must meet the admission requirements. Scholarships are usually awarded based on different criteria:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Nationality,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Financial need,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Previous Academic Achievement.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">You can check out scholarship opportunities on your chosen university\u2019s website. Make time to do some research to get helpful information.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Do you want to know about <a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/importance-of-age-for-admission-and-student-visa\/\">the Importance of Age for Admission and Student Visa<\/a>? read this article:<\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"KqiSWG1Ixj\"><p><a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/importance-of-age-for-admission-and-student-visa\/\">Importance of Age for Admission and Student Visa<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;Importance of Age for Admission and Student Visa&#8221; &#8212; Abroadin \" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/importance-of-age-for-admission-and-student-visa\/embed\/#?secret=93m82rHC0b#?secret=KqiSWG1Ixj\" data-secret=\"KqiSWG1Ixj\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Most Affordable Universities in the United Kingdom<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Following a governmental decision in 2017, UK universities are allowed to charge domestic students with tuition fees up to GBP 9250. At the same time, universities independently set their tuitions\u2019 policy for international scholars.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">There are universities in the UK, which charge the same minimum for international students as for the home students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">So international students can find affordable Bachelors and Masters programs in the United Kingdom, usually under 5000 EUR per year. But most of them are only available to EU\/EEA students at this cost.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Let&#8217;s look at some of the most affordable colleges and universities in the UK:<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University of Stirling<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.stir.ac.uk\/\">The University of Stirling<\/a> has built its reputation upon excellence and innovation. For its prospective students, it offers a high-quality education and a wide spectrum of study programs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Despite being a highly reputed, this university is definitely one of the cheapest universities in the UK. Undergraduate students at this university will be charged GBP 12140. Tuition fees at the postgraduate level vary between GBP 13650 to and 18970.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Queen Margaret University; UK Tuition Fees<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The campus of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.qmu.ac.uk\/\">the Queen Margaret University<\/a> is located just six minutes by train far from the wonderful city of Edinburgh, in the seaside town of Musselburgh.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">At this university, you\u2019ll find a wide range of study programs. The tuition it carries is fairly low in comparison to the British standard.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">For the upcoming academic year, international students at the undergraduate level will be charged with tuition fees between GBP 12500 and 13500, while those at the postgraduate level will be charged much less.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Southampton Solent University<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.solent.ac.uk\/\">The Southampton Solent University<\/a> study programs are sought after by numerous international scholars.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Its student population consists of students coming from almost 100 nationalities. The followings are tuition fees for international students in the upcoming academic year<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1564\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/london-city-name-collage-1.jpg\" alt=\"UK Tuition Fees\" width=\"1380\" height=\"920\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/london-city-name-collage-1.jpg 1380w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/london-city-name-collage-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads